      "id": "ev-s3",
      "type": "quiz",
      "title": "Knowledge Check — Crypto Glossary",
      "content": {
        "type": "quiz",
        "questions": [
          {
            "id": "q-ev-1",
            "type": "single",
            "question": "What does 'HODL' mean in crypto?",
            "options": [
              {
                "label": "A type of blockchain",
                "value": "A"
              },
              {
                "label": "Hold On for Dear Life — keeping your crypto instead of selling",
                "value": "B"
              },
              {
                "label": "A fee paid to miners",
                "value": "C"
              },
              {
                "label": "A way to borrow crypto",
                "value": "D"
              }
            ],
            "answer": [
              "B"
            ],
            "analysis": "HODL started as a typo for 'hold' that went viral. It means holding onto your crypto through price swings instead of panic-selling — a strategy many long-term investors swear by.",
            "points": 1
          },
          {
            "id": "q-ev-2",
            "type": "single",
            "question": "What is a 'bull market'?",
            "options": [
              {
                "label": "A market where prices are falling",
                "value": "A"
              },
              {
                "label": "A market where only bulls can trade",
                "value": "B"
              },
              {
                "label": "A market where prices are rising and people are buying",
                "value": "C"
              },
              {
                "label": "A market that is closed",
                "value": "D"
              }
            ],
            "answer": [
              "C"
            ],
            "analysis": "A bull market is when prices are trending upward. The name comes from the image of a bull charging forward with horns up. Bear market is the opposite — prices trending down.",
            "points": 1
          },
          {
            "id": "q-ev-3",
            "type": "single",
            "question": "What is a 'gas fee'?",
            "options": [
              {
                "label": "The cost of electricity to run a computer",
                "value": "A"
              },
              {
                "label": "A small fee paid to process a transaction on a blockchain",
                "value": "B"
              },
              {
                "label": "A tax charged by the government on crypto",
                "value": "C"
              },
              {
                "label": "The profit a trader makes on a trade",
                "value": "D"
              }
            ],
            "answer": [
